@startuml MagicLinkSSO-Gate-Flow

title Magic Link SSO Gate Flow

actor User
participant "Browser" as Browser
participant "Magic Link SSO Gate" as Gate
participant "SSO Server" as SSO
participant "Email Server" as Email
participant "Private Upstream\n(app or static site)" as Upstream

== Anonymous Request ==

User -> Browser: Open https://private.example.com/
Browser -> Gate: GET /
Gate -> Gate: Check auth cookie

alt Cookie exists and is valid
    Gate -> Upstream: Proxy request with forwarded identity headers
    Upstream --> Gate: HTML / assets / API / SSE / websocket handshake
    Gate --> Browser: Protected upstream response
else Cookie missing or invalid
    alt Direct-use enabled
        Gate --> Browser: Redirect to https://sso.example.com/signin\nwith normalized returnUrl + verifyUrl
        Browser -> SSO: GET /signin
        SSO --> Browser: Hosted sign-in page
        Browser -> SSO: Submit email address
    else Local Gate login enabled
        Gate --> Browser: Redirect to /_magicgate/login?returnUrl=...
        Browser -> Gate: GET /_magicgate/login
        Gate --> Browser: Local sign-in page
        Browser -> Gate: POST /_magicgate/signin
        Gate -> SSO: POST /signin\n{ email, normalized returnUrl, verifyUrl }
    end

    SSO -> SSO: Resolve site from returnUrl / verifyUrl\nand authorize email + default scope
    SSO -> Email: Send magic link
    Email --> User: Receive email

    User -> Email: Click magic link
    Email -> Browser: Open https://private.example.com/_magicgate/verify-email\n?token=...&returnUrl=...
    Browser -> Gate: GET /_magicgate/verify-email?token=...
    Gate -> SSO: GET /verify-email?token=...\n(Accept: application/json,\nX-Magic-SSO-Preview-Secret)
    SSO --> Gate: 200 JSON { email }
    Gate -> Gate: Validate preview JSON\nset temporary token cookie + signed CSRF cookie
    Gate --> Browser: Confirmation page\nwith token removed from URL
    Browser -> Gate: POST /_magicgate/verify-email\n{ csrfToken, returnUrl }
    Gate -> Gate: Validate same-origin signal + CSRF\nand read token from temporary cookie
    Gate -> SSO: POST /verify-email { token }
    SSO --> Gate: 200 JSON { accessToken }
    Gate -> Gate: Validate JWT locally\n(expected iss + aud + signature)
    Gate -> Gate: Clear temporary cookies\nand set Gate-managed auth cookie
    Gate --> Browser: Redirect to original returnUrl

    Browser -> Gate: GET /
    Gate -> Gate: Check auth cookie
    Gate -> Upstream: Proxy request with forwarded identity headers
    Upstream --> Gate: Protected response
    Gate --> Browser: Protected upstream response
end

== Authenticated Follow-up ==

Browser -> Gate: Subsequent request for asset / API / static file / SPA route
Gate -> Gate: Validate auth cookie
Gate -> Upstream: Proxy request with forwarded identity headers
Upstream --> Gate: Response
Gate --> Browser: Response

note over Gate, Upstream
The upstream can be a dynamic app-style service (`private1`) or a static site
(`private2`). In both cases, authentication stays in Gate and the upstream
remains unaware of the Magic Link SSO flow.
end note

@enduml
